In [66]:
walking_activity = training_data[training_data['Activity'] == 'WALKING']
# Reset the index for this dataframe
walking_activity = walking_activity.reset_index(drop=True)
In [67]:
# Set time series for each subject
time = 1
index = 0
time_series = np.zeros(walking_activity.shape[0])
for row_number in range(walking_activity.shape[0]):
    if (row_number == 0 
        or walking_activity.iloc[row_number]['subject'] == walking_activity.iloc[row_number - 1]['subject']):
        time_series[index] = time
        time += 1
    else:
        time_series[index] = 1
        time = 2
    index += 1
In [68]:
# Combine the time_series with the standing_activity dataframe
time_series_df = pd.DataFrame({ 'Time': time_series })
walking_activity_df = pd.concat([walking_activity, time_series_df], axis = 1)
In [69]:
colors = cm.rainbow(np.linspace(0, 1, len(walking_activity_df['subject'].unique())))

# Create plot for each subject, which will all be displayed overlapping on one plot
id = 0
for subject in walking_activity_df['subject'].unique():
    plt.rcParams.update({'figure.figsize': [40, 30], 'font.size': 24})
    plt.plot(walking_activity_df[walking_activity_df['subject'] == subject]['Time'], 
             walking_activity_df[walking_activity_df['subject'] == subject]['angle(X,gravityMean)'],
             c = colors[id], 
             label = 'Subject ' + str(subject),
             linewidth = 4)
    plt.xlabel('Time')
    plt.ylabel('Angle')
    plt.title('Angle between X and mean Gravity v/s Time for various subjects')
    plt.legend(prop = {'size': 24})
    id += 1
